.SH NAME
dotty-brewfile-sync - Make the machine match the Brewfile exactly.


.SH SYNOPSIS
\fBdotty brewfile sync [--force] [flags]\fP


.SH DESCRIPTION
Synchronise the machine with the Brewfile — install what's listed, upgrade
what's outdated, and remove (zap) what isn't listed. When anything would be
removed, dotty shows the list and asks first unless --force is set.


.SH OPTIONS
\fB--force\fP[=false]
	remove unlisted brews without asking

.PP
\fB-h\fP, \fB--help\fP[=false]
	help for sync


.SH OPTIONS INHERITED FROM PARENT COMMANDS
\fB--profile\fP=""
	profile to operate on (defaults to the active profile)


.SH EXAMPLE
.EX
  dotty brewfile sync
  dotty brewfile sync --force
.EE


.SH SEE ALSO
\fBdotty-brewfile(1)\fP
